502
00:40:56,250 --> 00:40:58,500
- Ji Soo. 
 - What's the matter?

503
00:40:58,500 --> 00:41:01,350
Jae Hyeon and the others are out at the slum we were helping in Hyeonjeo-dong.

504
00:41:01,350 --> 00:41:03,700
- They just called about something urgent.
 - A slum?

505
00:41:03,700 --> 00:41:06,540
Yes, it's similar to volunteering in rural areas, but in slums instead.

506
00:41:06,540 --> 00:41:07,980
You guys do that kind of work too?

507
00:41:07,980 --> 00:41:10,670
We may look shabby, but we're very active. I'll be off now, I don't have much time.

508
00:41:10,670 --> 00:41:12,250
Oh yeah, sure.

509
00:41:19,980 --> 00:41:24,650
Hey! Give me my ttakji back! 
  (T/N: ttakji is a toy, a folded paper tile)

510
00:41:24,650 --> 00:41:27,420
Give it back, give me my ttakji back!

511
00:42:05,970 --> 00:42:09,790
Get out of the way!

512
00:42:16,050 --> 00:42:18,870
Just knock it all down!

513
00:42:26,300 --> 00:42:28,080
 Yah!

514
00:42:28,080 --> 00:42:30,890
 These rascals! Break it all down!

515
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:33,810
 This...

516
00:44:00,670 --> 00:44:02,840
Did Yeong Woo not tell you?

517
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:04,620
What?

518
00:44:04,620 --> 00:44:06,850
He didn't tell you what we were here for?

519
00:44:08,040 --> 00:44:09,830
Your attire...

520
00:44:11,500 --> 00:44:14,290
Sorry, I didn't know.

521
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:17,940
You must've ruined your nice clothes.

522
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:21,440
Good work.

523
00:44:24,740 --> 00:44:29,080
Why do you protest...

524
00:44:29,930 --> 00:44:32,340
Why do you participate in demonstrations?

525
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:36,110
You don't have time to study or even to have fun like other people.

526
00:44:36,110 --> 00:44:38,320
You're constantly chased and getting hurt.

527
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:41,190
How can you live like that every day?

528
00:44:46,680 --> 00:44:49,460
I want to call the losing side, my side.

529
00:44:51,480 --> 00:44:54,940
Everyone always wants to call the winners side their side.

530
00:44:54,940 --> 00:44:57,400
So the losing side is always lonely and sad.

531
00:44:58,370 --> 00:45:03,770
Those who always lose no matter how many times they fight... I want to take their side.

532
00:45:13,690 --> 00:45:20,010
Taking the side of the ones who always lose no matter how many times they fight.

533
00:45:21,320 --> 00:45:23,680
That's what I learned.

534
00:45:25,760 --> 00:45:28,470
Do you have the leisure to take someone's side?

535
00:45:29,350 --> 00:45:32,730
You could end up losing too.

536
00:45:32,730 --> 00:45:35,010
I don't care.

537
00:45:35,010 --> 00:45:37,720
All this time, I haven't had much experience winning, anyway.

538
00:45:39,430 --> 00:45:45,100
I may have never won, but I've also never been ashamed.

539
00:45:46,780 --> 00:45:50,520
I don't want to change that. Especially if that's because of you.

540
00:46:25,590 --> 00:46:27,760
It was around here.

541
00:46:27,760 --> 00:46:30,110
What do you mean?

542
00:46:30,900 --> 00:46:35,700
Hyeonjeo-dong.  Where I last had my conscience.

543
00:46:40,410 --> 00:46:43,470
The fine dust levels are high today, Vice President.

544
00:46:44,930 --> 00:46:49,230
If it's about being noxious, I'll easily win against some measly fine dust.

545
00:46:49,230 --> 00:46:51,660
Come on, how can you say such thing?

546
00:46:51,660 --> 00:46:53,290
You're right.

547
00:46:54,350 --> 00:46:57,680
I guess the dust would be offended.

548
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:01,690
At least they don't interfere with the lives of others.

549
00:47:01,690 --> 00:47:04,230
Did something happen today?

550
00:47:11,490 --> 00:47:13,940
I want to be on your side.

551
00:47:15,230 --> 00:47:19,760
Since you're on the losing people's side, you must be lonely too.

552
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:22,300
So I'll be on your side.

553
00:47:25,210 --> 00:47:28,520
It'll be difficult being on my side. You won't be able to do it.

554
00:47:28,520 --> 00:47:35,090
Being in Hyeonjeo-dong today, my heart felt weird and it ached.

555
00:47:35,090 --> 00:47:38,580
But after hearing your story on top of that,

556
00:47:38,580 --> 00:47:41,650
something in here keeps resonating,

557
00:47:45,670 --> 00:47:48,640
and I feel something hot rising inside me.

558
00:47:52,370 --> 00:47:54,680
That's why I told you not to come.

559
00:47:55,460 --> 00:47:57,790
It doesn't suit you.

560
00:47:57,790 --> 00:48:01,200
There are many people on my side already, so you just go back where you used to be.

561
00:48:03,050 --> 00:48:06,530
I have to go to a meeting. Take the bus home.

